---
import ReviewLayout from '../../../layouts/ReviewLayout.astro';

const productName = "Best Digital Kitchen Scale for Portion Control";
const amazonUrl = "https://www.amazon.com/s?k=digital+kitchen+scale&ref=nb_sb_noss&tag=costcohotdogg-20";

const pros = [
  "0.1g precision for accurate tracking",
  "Tare function for easy container weighing",
  "Compact design fits in any kitchen drawer",
  "Affordable price point under $20",
  "Long battery life (6+ months)"
];

const cons = [
  "Small weighing surface limits bowl size",
  "LCD can be hard to read in bright light",
  "Plastic build feels less premium",
  "Auto-shutoff can be too quick (30 seconds)"
];

const relatedGuides = [
  { title: "Calories Without Bun", href: "/tutorials/calories-without-bun/", description: "Track your macros with precision using a kitchen scale." },
  { title: "Nutrition Calculator", href: "/tools/nutrition-calculator/", description: "Calculate nutrition for custom Costco food combinations." },
  { title: "Costco Hot Dog Nutrition", href: "/hot-dog/nutrition/", description: "Complete macro and micronutrient breakdown." },
  { title: "Diet Tips for Hot Dog Lovers", href: "/hot-dog/diet-tips/", description: "Enjoy your hot dog while staying on track." }
];
---

<ReviewLayout
  title={productName}
  description="Our top picks for affordable, accurate digital kitchen scales to help you track portions and macros with Costco foods."
  productName={productName}
  rating={4.5}
  priceRange="$12 - $55"
  pros={pros}
  cons={cons}
  verdict="For most Costco shoppers tracking macros, the Etekcity Digital Kitchen Scale offers unbeatable value at under $15. If you want premium precision and a sleek design, the OXO Good Grips Stainless Steel Scale is worth the upgrade."
  amazonUrl={amazonUrl}
  relatedGuides={relatedGuides}
>
  <h2>Why a Kitchen Scale Matters for Costco Shoppers</h2>
  <p>
    Costco is all about bulk buying, which makes portion control essential. A digital kitchen scale helps you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Accurately track macros and calories</li>
    <li>Divide bulk packages into proper serving sizes</li>
    <li>Follow recipes precisely (especially important for baking)</li>
    <li>Avoid overeating when faced with enormous Costco portions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Top Picks</h2>

  <h3>1. Etekcity Digital Kitchen Scale — Best Value</h3>
  <p>
    At under $15, the Etekcity scale delivers surprising accuracy (0.1g precision) and reliability. It's the scale we recommend for anyone starting their portion-tracking journey.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Price:</strong> $12–$15</li>
    <li><strong>Capacity:</strong> 11 lbs / 5 kg</li>
    <li><strong>Precision:</strong> 0.1g</li>
    <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Beginners and budget shoppers</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2. OXO Good Grips Stainless Steel — Best Premium</h3>
  <p>
    The OXO scale's pull-out display is a genius feature — it extends from the base so you can read the weight even with a large mixing bowl on top. The stainless steel surface is easy to clean and looks great on any counter.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Price:</strong> $49–$55</li>
    <li><strong>Capacity:</strong> 11 lbs / 5 kg</li>
    <li><strong>Precision:</strong> 0.1g</li>
    <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Serious home cooks and bakers</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3. Greater Goods Nourish — Best for Meal Prep</h3>
  <p>
    This scale includes a built-in nutrition calculator with codes for 2,000+ foods. While not as comprehensive as a smartphone app, it's handy for quick checks without pulling out your phone.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Price:</strong> $29–$35</li>
    <li><strong>Capacity:</strong> 11 lbs / 5 kg</li>
    <li><strong>Precision:</strong> 1g</li>
    <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Meal preppers who want quick nutrition data</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How We Tested</h2>
  <p>
    We evaluated each scale across these criteria:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Accuracy:</strong> Tested with calibrated 100g, 500g, and 1000g weights</li>
    <li><strong>Speed:</strong> Measured how quickly the reading stabilizes</li>
    <li><strong>Ease of use:</strong> Assessed button placement, display readability, and tare function</li>
    <li><strong>Durability:</strong> Dropped from counter height (12 times each) and checked for damage</li>
    <li><strong>Cleanup:</strong> Evaluated how easy the surface is to wipe clean</li>
  </ul>
</ReviewLayout>
